CSS Compass was designed with the intention of helping both incoming and current CSS students reach their goals. The development team sought to compile useful resources that they felt aided their own journey, so that new students would have a launchpad for becoming successful students/programmers.

The School of Engineering and Technology (SET) at the University of Washington Tacoma prepares our students to become future leaders in a variety of computer, electrical, mechanical and civil engineering fields. Students enrolled in the SET program go on to develop real world solutions in embedded systems, information technology, information systems, and computer software design, development and maintenance. The curriculum provides students the theoretical grounding to promote lifelong evolution in their field while also preparing them to become effective innovators and entrepreneurs.
